instruction: Analyze the loan-level data provided by issuers and identify any potential insights that can benefit ABS investors.
output: After analyzing the loan-level data provided by issuers, we have identified several potential insights that can be useful for ABS investors. The borrower credit score, cosigner, income and employment verification, loan term, balance, coupon, age and subvention, vehicle make, model, model year and condition when bought (new or used), and the full performance history have all been accounted for in the analysis. By examining this data, ABS investors can potentially gain new insights on the performance of the loans, the risk associated with them, and how they can effectively manage their investments based on these insights.
